# Tuscany 2026 — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the real values. Vite
# only exposes variables prefixed with `VITE_` to the browser
# bundle. Anything else stays server/build-side only.
#
# `.env.local` is gitignored. NEVER commit a real key.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default Gemini API key for the Gemininio chat. When set, every
# visitor of the site uses this key automatically — they don't have
# to paste their own.
#
# Get a free key at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# IMPORTANT — security trade-off:
#   This key gets baked into the JavaScript bundle at build time.
#   Anyone who view-sources the deployed site CAN extract it. Before
#   shipping, restrict the key in the AI Studio console:
#     - Application restrictions → HTTP referrers (websites)
#     - Add: https://tikel1.github.io/tuscany-2026/*
#   That alone won't stop a determined attacker (referer headers
#   can be spoofed) but it filters out all the casual scrapers.
#
# Leave this blank to fall back to the user-supplied-key flow
# (each user pastes their own on first chat).

VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# ElevenLabs (local scripts only — not exposed to the browser)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by:
#   npm run tts:attractions-he:eleven -- --force
#   npm run tts:italian-words-ex:eleven -- --force
# Model defaults to eleven_v3. Optional: ELEVEN_HE_VOICE_ID, ELEVEN_IT_WORDS_VOICE_ID,
# ELEVEN_HE_MODEL, ELEVEN_IT_WORDS_MODEL.
#
# ELEVEN_API_KEY=
